    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="410" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <head>No. 409.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morgan</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-06-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 19, 1883</date>.
                            (Received July 5.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 646.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Mexican Congress adjourned yesterday. The
                        important work done during the session was: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Making an appropriation for the expenses of a legation at
                                London.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Authorizing a settlement of the public debt.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Authorizing the President to contract a loan of twenty millions of
                                dollars.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>P. H. MORGAN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
